<head>CLOTH MATERIALS</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">布料</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>PLANTS USED FOR PRODUCING CLOTH.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The common material to make cloth from was má 麻 "hemp".</p>
<p>2. Gé 葛 "kudzu vine" was also commonly used in ancient times and the word is particularly common in SHI.</p>
<p>For other materials see HUANG JINGUI's detailed surveys.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
